---
import Layout from '~/layouts/MarkdownLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Privacy Policy',
  description: 'Privacy Policy for Schedule.Makeup explaining our data collection and protection practices.',
};
---

<Layout frontmatter={metadata}>

<p><em>Last Updated: March 2026</em></p>

<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
<p>Schedule.Makeup ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our website and vanity booking URL services (the "Service").</p>

<h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Personal Data:</strong> We collect names, email addresses, and business details voluntarily provided via our setup and contact forms.</li>
    <li><strong>Business Data:</strong> To operate the Service, we process your public business information, including your studio name and Google Business Profile links.</li>
    <li><strong>Payment Data:</strong> We use third-party processors (such as PayPal). We do not store your financial information or credit card numbers on our servers.</li>
    <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> We automatically collect standard log information, including IP addresses and browser types, via analytics tools (e.g., Splitbee or Google Analytics) to improve Service performance.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>We use the data collected to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Provision and maintain your custom vanity booking URL.</li>
    <li>Integrate your booking system with Google Search and Maps.</li>
    <li>Process payments and provide customer support.</li>
    <li>Analyze usage patterns to improve our mobile-first layouts.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Sharing of Information</h2>
<p>We do not sell your personal data. We only share information with third-party vendors necessary for hosting, domain routing, and payment processing. We may disclose information if required by law or to protect the safety and rights of our users.</p>

<h2>5. Data Security</h2>
<p>We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

<h2>6. Third-Party Links</h2>
<p>Your vanity URL may point to third-party booking tools. This Privacy Policy does not apply to those third-party sites. We encourage you to review their respective privacy policies.</p>

<h2>7. Governing Law</h2>
<p>This Privacy Policy and our privacy practices are governed by the laws of **the State of Delaware, United States**, without regard to its conflict of law principles. Any legal actions or proceedings related to this Privacy Policy shall be brought exclusively in the state or federal courts located in the State of Delaware.</p>

<h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
<p>You have the right to request access to the data we hold about you or request its deletion. To exercise these rights or to disconnect your vanity URL, please contact us directly.</p>

<h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last Updated" date at the top of the page will reflect the most recent changes.</p>

<h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us through our <a href="/contact">Contact Page</a>.</p>

</Layout>
